Commentary Text: Jadeja to Hetmyer, 1 run, full outside off, Hetmyer flicks to deep square and whoa, what happened there? Moeen juggles in the deep and the throw was wayward too, both batters thought of a second but decided against it in the end. Comedy of errors. Firstly there was confusion of yes-no for the second. Then they saw Moeen fire it into the middle of the pitch where no-one was there. No back up too, but a fielder ran and slid across to force the batters into hesitation again. Thakur collected in the deep and threw it to Dhoni to ensure it is just one run. Could have been easy two, but confusion meant the batters didn't risk it

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by du Plessis!! You gotta be really bold to take on Faf, the fielder. You better hit it over him. Left or right, he's gonna jump onto it like a leopard. Dropped on 42, Prithvi Shaw doesn't make the most of his opportunity. Jaddu released this more off the grip of thumb and index finger. A juicy toss up outside off, Prithvi Shaw goes for the inside out loft and got it off the toe, only to find one of the finest fielders - Faf - in the deep. Ran across to his left and completed the catch with a perfectly-timed dive. Prithvi Shaw c du Plessis b Jadeja 60(34) [4s-7 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Dhawan, out Caught by Dhoni!! There's the comeback from Hazlewood, CSK needed it, the openers were beginning to look too comfortable - shortened his length did Hazlewood and got the ball to seam away from outside off, Dhawan's feet went nowhere as he pushed away from his body. A thin edge is found and it's a straightforward catch for MS. After a couple of expensive overs, Hazlewood gets the much-needed wicket for Dhoni's men. Dhawan c Dhoni b Hazlewood 7(7) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Tom Curran to Dhoni, FOUR, short slower delivery outside off stump, Dhoni pulls behind square. Oh no one there and CSK are in their 9th IPL final. If you still have doubts of Dhoni the finisher, you might want to rethink! People were surprised to see him come above Jadeja especially with the captain not middling that well in recent times. But he hit that crucial six last over and an important four off that hat-trick ball to keep CSK in the hunt and then took the side over the line. CSK win with Jadeja not facing a ball. Wow!

Commentary Text: Rabada to Ruturaj Gaikwad, out Rayudu Run Out!! 1 run completed. Well, well. What a turnaround. CSK were coasting and suddenly they have thrown two wickets away. Firstly, Ruturaj Gaikwad mishit a pull shot to this shortish delivery, just over mid-wicket. The second was tight, but on. Rayudu couldn't quite skate back in time. But Shreyas Iyer did skate quickly to the ball and fire a good throw adjacent to the sticks. Very good from Rabada to come up to the stumps. The throw was so hard from Shreyas that it was taking Rabada back with the momentum, but KG managed to collect and ignite the stumps to catch Rayudu short. Shreyas Iyer has turned this match with his fielding. Rayudu run out (Shreyas Iyer/Rabada) 1(3)

Commentary Text: Tom Curran to Thakur, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! In the airrr, no distance. It's Shreyas Iyer again with the catch. The Thakur promotion doesn't work. Very, very smart bowling from Tom Curran. He landed the slower delivery wide of off stump and made the batter fetch the big hit. Thakur connected decently, would have gone all the way if it was full pace, but he didn't have the pace to work with and Shreyas ran across to his left to pouch that. Two wickets in the over. Game on! You don't see such funky moves from CSK in a big game. What's this going to do? Thakur c Shreyas Iyer b Tom Curran 0(1)

Commentary Text: Tom Curran to Uthappa, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! That looked so cool from Shreyas Iyer, but too close for comfort too. Remember Murali Vijay taking a nonchalant catch in the deep some years ago. The third ump has a close look at this one. Shreyas was probably just an inch from touching. Great composure to balance and then release the ball before crossing the line. Came back to take it easily. Tom Curran took pace off on this short of length delivery, Uthappa played the pull, too high. Iyer moved to his right from long-on. Axar came across from deep mid-wicket but the former never lost his focus. Ends a fantastic hand from Uthappa. Uthappa c Shreyas Iyer b Tom Curran 63(44) [4s-7 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Nortje to du Plessis, out Bowled!! Knocked him over! There's the early breakthrough for Delhi. 147.5kph! Too quick, even for an in-form Faf! Anrich Nortje is pumped up and rightly so. du Plessis b Nortje 1(2)
